# 2 Invariance of dynamics to transformation for identical memory patterns 

We will show that the application of the transformation in Eq. 5 on identical patterns (identical rows of $\Xi$ ) leaves the dynamics invariant. This has been previously demonstrated in Karin [7] and is included here for completeness.

Proposition B.3. Consider a subset $\mathcal{L}$ such that for each $r, s \in \mathcal{L}$ we have that $\Xi_{r}=\Xi_{s}$. Then $g(\boldsymbol{x}, \beta, \boldsymbol{Q}, \Xi, \boldsymbol{w})=$ $g_{\mathcal{L}}(\boldsymbol{x}, \beta, \boldsymbol{Q}, \Xi, \boldsymbol{w})$.

Proof. Consider the original dynamics for $x_{j}$ :

$$
\begin{aligned}
\dot{x}_{j} & =\sum_{i=1}^{K} q_{i, j} \frac{e^{w_{i}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{i, j x_{l}}}}{\sum_{k} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}}-x_{j}= \\
& =\sum_{i \in \mathcal{L}} \frac{q_{i, j} e^{w_{i}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{i, j x_{l}}}}{\sum_{k \in \mathcal{L}} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}+\sum_{k \notin \mathcal{L}} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}}+\sum_{i \notin \mathcal{L}} \frac{q_{i, j} e^{w_{i}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{i, j x_{l}}}}{\sum_{k \in \mathcal{L}} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}+\sum_{k \notin \mathcal{L}} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}}-x_{j}
\end{aligned}
$$

Now, under the transformation, and noting that for $k \in \mathcal{L}$ we have that $\Xi_{k}=\Xi_{\mathcal{L}}^{*}$, we have:

$$
\sum_{k \in \mathcal{L}} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}=\sum_{k \in \mathcal{L}} e^{w_{k}+\beta \Xi_{\mathcal{L}^{\prime}}^{*} *}=e^{w_{\mathcal{L}}^{*}+\beta \Xi_{\mathcal{L}^{\prime}}^{*} *}
$$

And:

$$
\sum_{k \in \mathcal{L}} q_{k, j} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}=e^{\beta \Xi_{\mathcal{L}^{\prime}}^{*} *} \sum_{k \in \mathcal{L}} q_{k, j} e^{w_{k}}=\left(Q_{\mathcal{L}}^{*}\right)_{j} e^{w_{\mathcal{L}}^{*}+\beta \Xi_{\mathcal{L}^{\prime}}^{*} *}
$$

And thus the transformed dynamics are given by:

$$
\begin{aligned}
\dot{x_{j}} & =\frac{\left(Q_{\mathcal{L}}^{*}\right)_{j} e^{w_{\mathcal{L}}^{*}+\beta \Xi_{\mathcal{L}^{\prime}}^{*} *}}{e^{w_{\mathcal{L}}^{*}+\beta \Xi_{\mathcal{L}^{\prime}}^{*} *}+\sum_{k \notin \mathcal{L}} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}}+\sum_{i \notin \mathcal{L}} q_{i, j} \frac{e^{w_{i}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{i, j x_{l}}}}{e^{w_{\mathcal{L}}^{*}+\beta \Xi_{\mathcal{L}^{\prime}}^{*} *}+\sum_{k \notin \mathcal{L}} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}}-x_{j} \\
& =\sum_{i \notin \mathcal{L} \text { or } i=\star} q_{i, j} \frac{e^{w_{i}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{i, j x_{l}}}}{\sum_{k} e^{w_{k}+\beta \sum_{i} \xi_{k, j x_{l}}}}-x_{j}
\end{aligned}
$$

And thus the dynamics are invariant under the transformation.
